descriptionHTML:
iCare Emotion Test could test your emotion and Autism-spectrum only by mobile!

MAIN FEATURES:
► Emotion Test
► Autism-spectrum Test
► Depression test

► Psychology Workout and Care

iCare Emotion Test is the emotion reading engine, which aims at providing accurate, smooth, powerful and easy accessible emotion recognizing and content matching services.

　　every one of us is generating more and more physiological data every minute, like pace, heart rate, breath, voice, etc. Therefore, iCare Emotion Test is dedicated to analyzing mega physiological data generated by users, determining emotions according to the analyzing reports and connecting them with relevant Internet content.

　　iCare Emotion Test focuses on developing the best emotion reading technology and the universal content matching algorithm in the world. We are committed to providing the emotion reading engine for developers and users by integrating the technologies of physical sign analyzing, Human nerve science, DM(Data Mining),machine learning, physical analysis, etc.

title: Emotional intelligence
summary: How are you feeling? Self-awareness, anger management and emotional development
description: The main goal of this application is to help you have full awareness of your feelings. Self-awareness is the first step for those seeking a high level of emotional intelligence. Most of the time, we do not stop to think about how we are feeling. Be aware of your emotions helps you take action to change the situation. In the reports, you can view your progress (emotional balance) separated by months. So you will know yourself better. You will get motivated whenever necessary. You will have more empathy and will have better professional and personal relationships.
descriptionHTML: The main goal of this application is to help you have full awareness of your feelings. Self-awareness is the first step for those seeking a high level of emotional intelligence. Most of the time, we do not stop to think about how we are feeling. Be aware of your emotions helps you take action to change the situation. In the reports, you can view your progress (emotional balance) separated by months. So you will know yourself better. You will get motivated whenever necessary. You will have more empathy and will have better professional and personal relationships.
comments: ['Its okay so far, but could you make a bit more elaborate pie chart, like include the feelings instead of others. Also, I have a suggestion, could you maybe add an option that explains feeling nothing. Like there are times when you feel nothing among the feelings that are given in the options. Some of the suggestions are kind of rude, so please work on that too. Overall I liked the app, but also include some tips instead of notifications. Thanks', "This app is really helpful.  I rated it a four though for two reasons.  When I press on the stress emotion a little pop up comes up at the bottom asking if the things I'm stressed about are valid.  Yes they are.  Dont trivialize my emotions.  Second the smaller items are put into an other section on the pie chart.  It would be helpful to be able to view more details on those.", 'I think it is really a brilliant app with reagrd to its idea. However, it would be better to have more emotions, more than one emotional choice and an option not to check worried. Other than that great work! Thanks! I dont feel alone anymore, ur app cares for me. :)', "Settings are very limited. It also inputs your info if you choose a feeling before you set your anxiety and you have to choose at least half a circle which I think is unfair as you may feel zero anxiety at the moment. Only been using this for two days but think it's cool just needs some improvements.", 'Designed to be simple and usable so that you really do make use of it a regular basis (it\'s most valuable when used regularly). Never seen anything like it before. Fantastic. Small criticisms: 1. Use of english is a bit off. He needs some proofreading done. 2. The graphs which show your emotional history are too limited. Especially the pie chart. Most of the time only 3 emotions are displayed on the pie chart. The other almost 50% represented simply as "other". Why not try a different type of chart, not pie? If these 2 things were fixed, I would pay to have adverts removed because I would know I would defo use it for a long time into the future.', 'Quite limited for now, you need more feelings to fulfill the app\'s purpose to it\'s maximum. "Other" feelings in report should be separate. I know it may be annoying to program but it would most likely get you better reviews. Please work on that']

title: Learn Emotions! How do I feel?
summary: Learning app for small children - learn emotions and express how you feel!
description: Learning app for small children - learn emotions and express how you feel!App contains photographs, drawn images of children mixed together with sounds to describe most common and simple emotions, feelings and needs: Happy, Angry, Sad, Playful, Hungry, Cold and others..App contains three modules:- select an emotion from a list of icons to express how the child feels now- list of cards for learning emotions- a quiz where a child must find a match for real photograph from several drawn emotion iconsApp contains advertisements, advertising content is friendly to children! Creators of the app consider their product to be created for children with special learning needs and are open to request for personal modification of the product by user requests. Regarding specific customization of the product (like extra emotions of personalized content) and other matter please use email in the app description bellow.Reviews and direct feedback is always welcome!Developed by Lukas and Erika, EnL Design studio
descriptionHTML:
Learning app for small children - learn emotions and express how you feel!

App contains photographs, drawn images of children mixed together with sounds to describe most common and simple emotions, feelings and needs: Happy, Angry, Sad, Playful, Hungry, Cold and others..

App contains three modules:

- select an emotion from a list of icons to express how the child feels now
- list of cards for learning emotions
- a quiz where a child must find a match for real photograph from several drawn emotion icons

App contains advertisements, advertising content is friendly to children!

Creators of the app consider their product to be created for children with special learning needs and are open to request for personal modification of the product by user requests. Regarding specific customization of the product (like extra emotions of personalized content) and other matter please use email in the app description bellow.

Reviews and direct feedback is always welcome!

Developed by Lukas and Erika,
EnL Design studio

title: Emotion
summary: Emotion is for people suffering from depression.
description: Emotion is for people suffering from depression. With this application, you have an easy-to-use tool to help you understand depression better and to assist you throughout your progress to recovery. Emotion is not intended as a substitute for your doctor, who alone is qualified to diagnose and treat depression, but only to help you keep track of your progress and, if you wish, to share your results with your doctor. Emotion has the following features: Understanding depression To help you better understand the disease through two sub-sections: - What is Depression? - Steps to take My progress To monitor and track your progress until recovery: - ‚ÄúTrack my progress‚Äù, a selection of questions to be answered simply by using a drag-and-drop cursor to indicate your current state. - ‚ÄúMy results‚Äù, keep track of your improvement day after day. If you wish, you can then show your results to your doctor and therefore facilitate the development of a fruitful exchange. Go further To find information and advice: - ‚ÄúSharing experience‚Äù: Get testimonies from former depressed patients or their families. - ‚ÄúLifestyle advice‚Äù: Suggestions of things to do that might help you to recover. - ‚ÄúRelaxation techniques‚Äù: Videos that may help to manage the effects of stress and anxiety, and relieve body tension, during or even after the disease. My profile To customize your Emotion app: - ‚ÄúMy checklist‚Äù: Addresses, questions to ask, treatments and appointments you want to note. - ‚ÄúMy Alerts‚Äù: To remind you to fill in your questionnaire Other Find the Emotion app user manual as well as the terms of use. Emotion was supported by a grant from Servier.
descriptionHTML:
Emotion is for people suffering from depression.

With this application, you have an easy-to-use tool to help you understand depression better and to assist you throughout your progress to recovery.

Emotion is not intended as a substitute for your doctor, who alone is qualified to diagnose and treat depression, but only to help you keep track of your progress and, if you wish, to share your results with your doctor.


Emotion has the following features:

Understanding depression
To help you better understand the disease through two sub-sections:
- What is Depression?
- Steps to take

My progress
To monitor and track your progress until recovery:
- “Track my progress”, a selection of questions to be answered simply by using a drag-and-drop cursor to indicate your current state.
- “My results”, keep track of your improvement day after day. If you wish, you can then show your results to your doctor and therefore facilitate the development of a fruitful exchange.

Go further
To find information and advice:
- “Sharing experience”: Get testimonies from former depressed patients or their families.
- “Lifestyle advice”: Suggestions of things to do that might help you to recover.
- “Relaxation techniques”: Videos that may help to manage the effects of stress and anxiety, and relieve body tension, during or even after the disease.

My profile
To customize your Emotion app:
- “My checklist”: Addresses, questions to ask, treatments and appointments you want to note.
- “My Alerts”: To remind you to fill in your questionnaire

Other
Find the Emotion app user manual as well as the terms of use.

Emotion was supported by a grant from Servier.

title: Emotion and Coping Game
summary: An app that helps parents and kids play a game that teaches about emotions.
description: Help your kids learn emotion identification and coping skills!The Emotion and Coping Game is an app based on a game created by the developer as a way to help kids learn how to identify emotions and what coping skills they can use when they experience a "difficult" emotion. It's meant to be flexible, so you can play how you want! Not sure of a good way to play? There are suggested gameplay instructions included in the app.The app will display a random emotion (i.e., happy, mad, sad, scared), and a number. Players take turns describing a situation that made them feel that emotion, then they can earn points, move the number of spaces, or however else you want to play. If the emotion is a "difficult" one (i.e., mad, sad, scared), the app allows you to have a random coping skill card played. By demonstrating the listed skill, the negative points from the "difficult" emotion are cancelled out and the player can move forward!While there is no research on this specific app, the developer is a doctoral student in clinical child psychology who has used the game as a part of therapy with kids. It's easy to play, and kids find it to be a fun way to discuss emotions!Features:- Customize the coping skills! The app supports enabling/disabling the included coping skills- Support to add your own coping skills- Customize the appearance! Colors can be customized.- Support for profiles of multiple users/players! Just switch players, and the colors and coping skill settings automatically switch.- Diverse representations of emotions- Information about the emotions and coping skills (to help kids learn about them)- App shortcuts to allow for going straight to the section you're interested in- Set daily reminders so you can easily remember to help your kids work on learning these skills
descriptionHTML:
Help your kids learn emotion identification and coping skills!

The Emotion and Coping Game is an app based on a game created by the developer as a way to help kids learn how to identify emotions and what coping skills they can use when they experience a "difficult" emotion. It's meant to be flexible, so you can play how you want! Not sure of a good way to play? There are suggested gameplay instructions included in the app.

The app will display a random emotion (i.e., happy, mad, sad, scared), and a number. Players take turns describing a situation that made them feel that emotion, then they can earn points, move the number of spaces, or however else you want to play. If the emotion is a "difficult" one (i.e., mad, sad, scared), the app allows you to have a random coping skill card played. By demonstrating the listed skill, the negative points from the "difficult" emotion are cancelled out and the player can move forward!

While there is no research on this specific app, the developer is a doctoral student in clinical child psychology who has used the game as a part of therapy with kids. It's easy to play, and kids find it to be a fun way to discuss emotions!

Features:
- Customize the coping skills! The app supports enabling/disabling the included coping skills
- Support to add your own coping skills
- Customize the appearance! Colors can be customized.
- Support for profiles of multiple users/players! Just switch players, and the colors and coping skill settings automatically switch.
- Diverse representations of emotions
- Information about the emotions and coping skills (to help kids learn about them)
- App shortcuts to allow for going straight to the section you're interested in
- Set daily reminders so you can easily remember to help your kids work on learning these skills

descriptionHTML:
Specifically designed for children who may have difficulty interpreting facial expressions, such as autism, Down syndrome and other visual learners. Helping them to understand emotions and react appropriately in social situations.

Also promotes:

• Word recognition
• Independent learning
• Language acquisition
• Fine motor skills
• Cause and effect understanding

Includes 10 languages:

• English (US)
• English (UK)
• Afrikaans
• Catalan
• Croatian
• French
• German
• Norwegian
• Polish
• Spanish

Consists of specifically designed images of 8 faces, with matching written and spoken words with a choice of lower or upper case letters.

Designed to be used alongside the other apps in our Touch series: Touch-Words, Touch-Colors, Touch-Shapes, Touch-Animals and Touch-Numbers.

Children can then progress to our highly configurable and easily personalized follow-on apps, Special Words and Special Stories.

Designed for tablets and smartphones. Contains no ads, in-app purchases or external links, collects no data, and doesn’t require an Internet connection.

Special iApps is a multi-award-winning nonprofit social enterprise that specializes in creating apps for those with learning disabilities and additional needs.
